<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>38-756.01</num>
  <heading>Rules.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>The Mayor, pursuant to <cite path="2|5|I">subchapter I of Chapter 5 of Title 2</cite> [<cite path="§2-501">§  2-501</cite> et seq.], shall issue rules to implement the provisions of this chapter.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>Each local education agency may advise the Mayor with respect to all proposed matters or rules issued pursuant to this chapter.</text>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 19-142" type="History" path="§601">June 19, 2012, D.C. Law 19-142, § 601, 59 DCR 3642</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
